  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What has replaced CGI (common gateway interface) in today's web?",
  "response": "In today's web, CGI (Common Gateway Interface) has largely been replaced by more modern technologies and frameworks that offer better performance, scalability, and ease of use. Some of the key technologies that have replaced CGI include:\n\n1. **Server-Side Frameworks**: Frameworks such as Node.js, Django (Python), Ruby on Rails, Laravel (PHP), and ASP.NET have become popular for building dynamic web applications. These frameworks provide robust ecosystems and tools to manage web servers effectively.\n\n2. **RESTful APIs**: REST (Representational State Transfer) has become a standard for designing networked applications. APIs designed with REST principles allow better separation of client and server, improve scalability, and enhance the modularity of services.\n\n3. **Single Page Applications (SPAs)**: Technologies such as Angular, React, and Vue.js allow the development of client-side applications that interact with the server primarily through APIs, reducing the need for server-side rendering that CGI facilitated.\n\n4. **WebSockets and Real-Time Communication**: WebSockets enable real-time, bidirectional communication between the client and server, which is crucial for applications like chat services and live data feeds. This has largely replaced the need for CGI in such scenarios.\n\n5. **Microservices Architecture**: Instead of monolithic applications that might use CGI, many modern applications are built using microservices, where each service can be developed independently using the most suitable technology.\n\n6. **Serverless Computing**: Platforms like AWS Lambda, Azure Functions, and Google Cloud Functions allow developers to run code without managing servers, providing an alternative to the traditional server-side CGI scripts.\n\nThese technologies offer improved efficiency, easier maintenance, and greater flexibility compared to CGI, making them more suitable for the demands of modern web applications.",
